The '''Florence Falls''' ([[Indigenous languages of Australia|Aboriginal]]: '''''Karrimurra''''') is a [[Waterfall#Types|segmented waterfall]] on the Florence Creek located within the [[Litchfield National Park]] in the [[Northern Territory]] of [[Australia]]. 

==Location and features==
[[Image:Florence Falls, "a spiritual place", sign post.jpg|thumb|left|A sign post near the falls.]]
The waterfall descends from an elevation of {{convert|64|m}} [[Australian Height Datum|above sea level]] via a series of segmented tiers that range in height between {{convert|9.8|-|15|m}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bonzle.com/c/a?a=p&p=253148&cmd=sp|title=Map of Florence Falls, NT|work=Bonzle Digital Atlas of Australia|accessdate=17 May 2014}}</ref> Accessed by sealed road, the falls are found near the northern boundary of the national park, approximately {{convert|80|km}} south of [[Darwin, Northern Territory|Darwin]]. 

A sign post at Florence Falls mentions two walks for hiking. The 'Shady Creek Walk' is graded easy with a distance of {{convert|1.2|km}} return. The 'Florence Creek Walk' is also graded easy with a distance of {{convert|3.2|km}} return. The Florence Falls plunge pool is listed as "great for a refreshing swim" besides the usual safety warnings.

